process.on('SIGTERM', () => server.close(() => process.exit(0)));
```

### 7. Don't start the server on `require`
Currently `require('./app')` calls `app.listen`, which breaks tests and can bind ports unexpectedly. Split into `app.js` (export app) and `server.js` (start it), or guard with `if (require.main === module)`.

### 8. Other small hardening items
- Use HTTPS in production (terminate at a proxy or use `https.createServer`).
- Set `NODE_ENV=production` to disable verbose Express errors.
- Add request logging (`morgan` or `pino-http`) with redaction of tokens/cookies.
- Pin dependency versions and run `npm audit` / Dependabot.
- Add authentication (e.g., JWT or session) before exposing anything user-specific.

